Today, UPB is the only British-style brass band in Utah. Under the direction of Dr. Todd Fiegel, the Utah Premiere Brass consists of thirty prfessional musiciams from around the state.````The brilliant blend of UPB's traditional brass instruments features remarkable ranges of whisper-soft passages to mighty fortissimos, lightning-fast phrases to beautifully potent melodies, and glorious timbres to breathless climaxes. description: Dinnington Colliery Band was formed in 1904 by miners from County Durham,  drafted into Dinnington to help with the sinking of the new colliery shaft.  Following the closure of the colliery in 1992, the band faced financial hardship, and their struggle for survival was recognized by the BBC when the band were  selected as ‘A Band for Britain’ - a three part documentary broadcast on BBC2 in March 2010.``In March , the Band won the 4th Section of the  Yorkshire Regional Championships in Bradford, and will represent Yorkshire at the National Brass Band Championships of Great Britain in September.

A championship section brass band based in the heartland of the banding world, Yorkshire. The band regularly competes against the world famous Brighouse & Rastrick and Black Dyke Bands.````Since its formation in 1977 the band has had many proud and enjoyable moments during its 32 year history and they continue to come! We are thrilled to be part of the Spa’s Bandstand series and MD Michael Howley, will ensure that an exciting programme of entertaining music is performed to suit all tastes.

Formed in 1989, EYMS quickly achieved Championship status, notably winning the Senior Cup in 2002 & 2008, and 2008 & 2009 Kippax Entertainment Championships. The Band participated in the 2009 French Open Championships, winning the March Contest and have also toured the Netherlands. Conducted by Musical Director Alan Morrison, the programme will cover a selection of music to suit every mood.

The Hunmanby Silver Band was formed in 1919 by Dennis Bailey. During the 1960s the band ceased operation due to compulsory conscription and restarted in 1979 with some members of Filey Silver Band who had also folded. We are one of the few remaining full complement brass bands operating on the North Yorkshire coastal strip, with emphasis on entertainment and enjoyment. The band remains very active and gives many public performances. We are an open door band and welcome new members and visiting musicians to our rehearsals.

The Ironbridge Gorge Brass Band Festival takes place over the weekend of 14 and 15 July 2012. Now in its eighth year, this free family event showcases some of the finest brass bands from Shropshire and the surrounding counties. This year, a conductor's baton representing one of the five Olympic rings will be arriving in style at the festival and bands will be participating in 'Brass the Baton', a London 2012 inspire project which is part of the 2012 Cutural Olympiad. Throughout the two days, brass bands take to the stage, performing to 4,000 people over the course of the weekend. Admission to the daytime festivals is free (from 11am to 5.45pm) and on the saturday night a ticketed charity gala concert will take place with all proceeds being donated to the Seven Hospice. ````For more information about the festival, please visit:``www.ironbridgebandfestival.co.uk``or follow on twitter @ironbridgebrass

description: The full band will be performing alongside the wonderful and talented Soprano Vocalist - Denise Leigh in the grand setting of Derby Cathedral in support of the Royal National Institute of Blind People. This is the second time the band have been on stage with Denise and for those who remember the last time you are in for a real treat! Also making a guest appearance will be the UK National Champion Accordianist, Stefan Andrusyschyn - you will be amazed! ````"Denise Leigh is the winner of channel 4s Operatunity: a nationwide search to find an amateur singer who could be trained intensively, terrified, have cameras stuck in their face, and survive long enough to sing the role of Gilda in Verdis Rigoletto at the home of ENO, the London Coliseum."````Featured in the evening will be Karl Jenkins The Armed Man, in addition to a new work for 2012, written by the Brass European Champion Composer Paul McGhee, especially for the bands 20th anniversary celebrations. Other music by Rossini and Paul Lovatt-Cooper will be in the programme together with a varied selection from both band and guests.````The concert will commence at 19:30````Tickets are priced at £10, or save 10% and buy in advance for only £9.````Go to www.derwentbrass.com to buy online now!````They are also available from both:````•Neville Bros Music, Babington Lane, Derby either in store or by phoning 01332 290762.``•Fould Music, 40 Iron Gate, Derby``Venue address: Derby Cathedral, 18-19 Iron Gate, Derby, DE1 3GP````For more on the Royal Institute of the Blind go to www.rnib.org.uk````For more on the wondeful talents of Denise Leigh go to www.deniseleigh.com````We look forward to seeing you there
